<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870715-0015 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:</HL><SO>  </SO><IN> ICEE-USA </IN><TEXT>07/15/87WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)ICY JJSFTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)   ICEE-USA said it agreed to borrow $4 million from Jandamp;J Snack Foods Corp. in exchange for a subordinated note convertible into 666,667 ICEE common shares at $6 a share. Jandamp;J, a Pennsauken, N.J.-based snack foods concern, currently holds a 45% stake in Anaheim, Calif.-based ICEE; it would have a 61% stake in the frozen beverage company after conversion of the note. ICEE said it also will give Jandamp;J warrants to purchase an additional 200,000 shares at $6 a share, boosting its stake to 64%. ICEE said it will use the funds to pay off bank debt and for current operations. </TEXT></DOC>